lenders.occupational_info:
We repair auto vehicles in the Cityview area of Fort Worth, TX.  My wife & I worked for this business prior to us buying it in Jan 2008.  We have been in business for 1 &1/2 yrs now but working this specific location for over 3 1/2 years.  We have great customers that we do our best to help and make payment arrangements with if needed.  We strive to give great customer satisfaction and a sincere friendly experience with our small business.
During this economic slow down, we have experienced cash flow problems. My mother came to assist me with the Buy Sell and establishment of this business in late 2007, assisted with the organization of operations, accounting, CPA selection and corporate fillings.  She became ill with her Multiple Sclerosis and was unable to assist for several months.  She also had to have surgery on her C-spine to repair disc & other issues involving the spinal canal.  She is now able to help us get our accounting methods improved & simplified which will assist in time management, better business decisions and ability to keep providing jobs. She will be able to help with marketing and accounting at home as we now are setup with QuickBooks Online.  This will give my wife and myself more time to concentrate on giving our customers our very best and giving back to the community.  We employee 2 full time and 2 part-time employees but would like to hire more.  We need operating cash for marketing and reorganizing our accounting and payables methods.  Since we are younger and have experienced new business obstacles, we have learned but cannot go for traditional loans at this time.  I work on vehicles myself and my wife works the front counter and back office as well. We work Monday - Saturday and care about our customers and this world we live in.  My wife is bilingual and is great working with people.  She hears what they need and does everything she can so we can help them get back on the road, back to work or what ever their automotive needs are. We would like to be able to get a used car license in the future to add another service to our customers.  We have been able to help our customers save by being able to repair vehicles that many would have not tried to fix. My employees are like family.  They go through each day with us with hope and determination. As stated before we are truly a family business.  Our accounting office also accommodates our 3 beautiful children when they are not in school or with their grandparents.  We love this Kiva concept and hope to get loans that we will repay and become a continual lender as well.  We will be spreading the word about this website to all we know.  Thank you Kiva for this opportunity.  Gabe Randall, Randall's Automotive Services, Fort Worth, TX
